URN:CornellLabOfOrnithology:EBIRD:OBS260230126	2017-08-16 00:24:17	7816	species	Sharp-shinned Hawk	Accipiter striatus			110				United States	US	Nevada	US-NV	Elko	US-NV-007	US-NV_971	9			Goshutes Hawkwatch	L808562	H	40.4253985	-114.2709489	1987-09-21	08:00:00	obsr45447	S18824024	Stationary	P21	EBIRD	540			4	0		0	1	0		In the fall of 1987, I was the official hawk counter on the Goshute Mtns Raptor Project. These are my data from the report I filed with the USFWS. This was a special day. Anticipating a Big Day, I had 3 assistants. Also, as was occasionally the case, we added an additional hour. The falcons, especially Peregrine Falcon were prone to pass later in the afternoon (as late as 6pm). The result was 17 species of raptor matching the then Big Day record published by the American Birding Association. Our total was subsequently published within the ABA record. To my knowledge, this stands as the greatest US tally for a stationary count.
